#React useId Hook

What is useId?
 ->  useId is a React Hook that generates a stable, unique ID for a component instance.

It is mainly used to:
          Link labels with inputs
          Avoid ID collisions
          Work correctly with Server-Side Rendering (SSR)

Example - 

import { useId } from "react";

function LoginForm() {
  const emailId = useId();
  const passwordId = useId();

  return (
    <form>
      <label htmlFor={emailId}>Email</label>
      <input id={emailId} type="email" />

      <label htmlFor={passwordId}>Password</label>
      <input id={passwordId} type="password" />
    </form>
  );
}


Why this matters:
      Screen readers rely on htmlFor
      Improves accessibility (a11y)
      No ID conflicts even with multiple forms
